   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">the basic stratagy of Memory Lapse is to get EVU out first turn if able and try to fill your hand with useful cards, then just throw out a massive army of small creatures to overwealm your opponent. You could call it a no-brainer,but as i read in an article about a week ago, which i think everyone should read, playing a winning deck is 50% deck content and 50% common sense.   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
